wikipedia_page.main: Thomas Collins (16 April 1882 – July 1929) was a Scottish footballer, who played for Heart of Midlothian, Bathgate, East Fife and Tottenham Hotspur.The full back transferred to Tottenham from Hearts in 1910 for a fee of £825. Collins made a total of 122 appearances in all competitions for Spurs and scored a solitary goal for the club between 1910 and 1915.
